-- Conditions `Favorable' for Monsoon to Advance, India's Weather Bureau Says
-- Madelene Pearson
-- 2010-06-14T04:39:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/conditions-favorable-for-monsoon-to-advance-india-s-weather-bureau-says.html

          
          
             Conditions are ‘favorable’ for
further advance of the monsoon into parts of India’s biggest
sugar cane, cotton and oilseeds growing states, a weather
forecaster said.  
 The rains may advance into parts of Maharashtra, Karnataka
and Andhra Pradesh, parts of Gujarat and Chhattisgarh and some
parts of Orissa, the India Meteorological Department said on its
website today.  
